newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see nearby mid-protein trades.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see nearby mid-protein trades.

text.p: The European meals and feeds market saw increased demand for nearby mid-protein material this afternoon, while soymeal was barely discussed due to a stronger dollar and a sharply lower Chicago soymeal futures opening, market sources said.

"Most of the mid-protein deals was technical covering and done for afloat and July shipment, with sellers rolling forward positions. We also saw some activity in citruspulp and EU rapemeal as these products are relatively cheap," a broker said.
Only one trade was reported in soymeal at $257 a tonne cif Rotterdam for afloat Argentine soymeal pellets.

Afloat Argentine sunmeal pellets traded at $126 and $127 from different vessels. July shipment traded from $122 to $125 a tonne cif Rotterdam, up $7 from yesterday. Aug/Sept traded at $122 and Oct/Dec at $126.50 a tonne cif.
Afloat citruspulp pellets changed hands at $74 a tonne cif Rotterdam and Oct/Dec at $80, the lowest level this year and some 30 per cent down from April.
Au/Oct EU rapemeal traded at 22.50 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine and Nov/Jan at 23.75 marks fob lower Rhine.--KAREL LUIMES + 31 20 504 5832.
